VITALIS UGOH CALABAR – Cross River State government has signed a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) with the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) and Rice Farmers Association of Nigeria (RIFAN) for the supply of multi-billion Naira rice seeds to farmers in Nigeria. The state Commissioner for Agriculture, Okon Nyong Owuna signed for the state, CBN representative, Tony Ifechukwu signed on behalf of the apex bank just as RIFAN National President, Alhaji Aminu Muhammad Goronyo signed on behalf of the association. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network At the event which held at the Executive chamber of the governor’s office, Calabar, Cross River State Governor, Sir Ben Ayade reiterated his commitment to ending unemployment in the state through Agro- industrialisation policy of his administration. He disclosed that his administration is to produce about 160,000 rice farmers with government assisting them with all the farm inputs, including clearing the forest, preparing the land, levelling the land, providing the seedlings. “We need to clear more forests to expand rice production. We need the support of CBN, we need the support of RIFAN. CBN has a major role to play in ensuring peace and stability in this country through food security”.